Dev grew up in one of Kyrgyzstan’s most prominent families, had attended university and was working as a television hostess. Then she discovered her true passion and calling—becoming a travelling missionary based in Bahrain—where she now leads mass events and works with new believers at international camping events globally.

As a nature lover, she especially loved the park around where her flat was located, always visiting it daily. Being of Russian heritage, she often encountered immigrants passing through the shelter, interacting with them but was shocked to learn they did nothing to protect these women.

“The situation in Russia is not much better, because as women increasingly acknowledge the right to control their own fertility, medieval laws for preventing abortion are being introduced en masse,” Dev tells Khaama Press.

“When I found this place and saw the women waiting in line outside, heads covered, not allowed to be with among other women waiting—not being allowed to talk among themselves, I knew I needed to do more.”
